history.content:
In this short study, you will be asked to complete some simple data exploration on a web-hosted application (no installation needed). Please email yifanwu@berkeley.edu to sign up/ask for more details (please include `Chronicles User Study` in the email title).   Recruiting through end of Jun!

For context: I'm a phd student at UC Berkeley in the database group studying tools for data scientists! This work is with Prof. Joe Hellerstein (whom you might know from CS186)

Requirements: you should be familiar with reading common data visualizations, and be able to use the interactive visualization here https://square.github.io/crossfilter/ (after learning how it works in a few minutes)--- we'll be using a similar tool and I will assume that you will be familiar with "cross-filter" visualizations.
Thanks!
history.subject: Data Visualization/Analysis 30 min User Study ($15 Amazon Credit)
